This paper is about model-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for search-control in Dyna, which is a well-known architecture for model-based RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the properties of different sampling distributions, which suggests a connection to control theory and system identification, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for hill climbing, which is a common optimization technique used in neural networks and other machine learning models, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
